This Java file, `AudioAttributesImplApi21Parcelizer`, is part of the Android Support Library's `v4.media` compatibility package. Its primary function is to serve as a static utility for serializing (`write`) and deserializing (`read`) instances of `AudioAttributesImplApi21` using Android's `VersionedParcel` mechanism. It acts as a direct proxy or compatibility wrapper, delegating all operations to its equivalent class in the `androidx.media` package. Within the context of a payment processing application, this file represents low-level Android framework boilerplate for managing audio-related settings, not directly involved in financial transactions, user authentication, or sensitive data handling.

[DETAILED LOGIC FLOW]
The `AudioAttributesImplApi21Parcelizer` class is declared as `public final` and resides in the `android.support.v4.media` package, indicating its role as an internal library component, reinforced by the `@RestrictTo({RestrictTo.Scope.LIBRARY})` annotation. It extends `androidx.media.AudioAttributesImplApi21Parcelizer`, signifying a compatibility bridge or direct delegation pattern common in Android's support libraries.

