    *   `private static int getMaxWidth(ResultPoint resultPoint, ResultPoint resultPoint2)`: Computes the absolute difference in X-coordinates between two `ResultPoint` objects, representing the width. Returns 0 if either point is null.
    *   `private static int getMinCodewordWidth(ResultPoint[] resultPointArr)`: Similar to `getMaxCodewordWidth` but calculates the minimum codeword width, using nested calls to `getMinWidth`.
    *   `private static int getMinWidth(ResultPoint resultPoint, ResultPoint resultPoint2)`: Computes the absolute difference in X-coordinates, returning `Integer.MAX_VALUE` if points are null to ensure `Math.min` behaves correctly.

